<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/ansel-wong> <http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml/vocab#license> <https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/doc/open-government-licence/version/3/> .
<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/ansel-wong> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "Ansel Wong is a Trinidadian cultural and political activist, who has been influential in many organisations particularly in the black community in the UK, where he has been based since the 1960s. He is the former Chair of the Notting Hill Carnival Board and founder of Elimu Mas Band. He is also an educationist and academic, and in a wide-ranging career has worked at senior levels in various organisations in the public and charitable sectors, including with the Windrush Foundation established in 1996 by Arthur Torrington."@en .
